Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim,
peel, and cut @parsnip{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel,
and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have
1 TBSP.

Toss carrots, parsnips, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle
of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with salt
and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add steak and cook until browned and cooked through, 5-7 minutes per side.

Turn off heat; transfer steak to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you
have 2 tsp.

> Swap in steak for pork; cook to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add minced onion and
chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken demi-glace{1} and @water{¼%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until
slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

Slice steak crosswise.

Divide steak and veggies between plates. Top steak with sauce and serve.

> Thinly slice steak against the grain.